<chapter xml:id="ch15-numerical-and-computational-methods-dimension-11-" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Numerical and Computational Methods (Dimension 11)</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>This chapter explores a crucial dimension of the quantum framework. Covers variational methods, tensor networks, Monte Carlo techniques, density functional theory, and modern computational approaches.</p>
  </introduction>
  <section><title>Overview</title>
    <p>This chapter continues development of the 11-dimensional quantum framework. Key concepts and applications are developed systematically.</p>
  </section>
  <section><title>Core Content</title>
    <p>Detailed treatment of major topics and techniques for this domain of quantum mechanics.</p>
  </section>
